# ============================================================================
# FORMAT A — NEW (orthogonal 5-type: $DIALOGUE $GRAMMAR $SELECT $PRODUCE $CHAT)
#
# Refinements rolled in:
#  - AUDIO is per LINE / per item (cassette clip, played in full), not per figure.
#    Clip naming pattern: bk04-l1a-f<fig>-<item>[-p|-a|-fb].mp3
#    (To avoid bulk, per-item AUDIO is shown fully in Fig 1–2 and as the first
#     item elsewhere; "# +AUDIO per item" marks where the rest follow suit.)
#  - $SELECT may declare a SHARED option pool once at the activity level; items
#    then only give ANSWER. A per-item OPTION/OPTION_IMAGE overrides the pool.
#  - $PRODUCE defaults: INPUT: speak, CHECK: reveal — omit unless overriding.
#  - FEEDBACK only where it adds value (explanation or a fuller model); omitted
#    when it would just echo the chosen option.
# ============================================================================

$MODULE ALC Book 4 — Lesson 1A: Sports and Games
DIOCO_DOC_ID: lc_alc_lla_bk4_l1a
DESCRIPTION: Talking about sports, games, and where people live (past and present).
TARGET_LANG_G: en
HOME_LANG_G: en
VOICE_DEFAULT: aoede | Clear, friendly American English narrator

$LESSON Lesson 1A

# --- Figure 1: repeat vocabulary — each item separate, each with its own clip ---
$DIALOGUE Figure 1: Sports and Games
REPEAT
INTRO: Look at the pictures and repeat the words and sentences.
INSTRUCTION: Listen and repeat.

VOCAB: play
VOCAB: game
VOCAB: ball
LINE: The children play a game with their ball. {page_007_001.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f1-01.mp3}

VOCAB: football
LINE: Sam plays football every day. {page_007_002.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f1-02.mp3}

VOCAB: baseball
LINE: George plays baseball on weekends. {page_007_003.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f1-03.mp3}

VOCAB: tennis
LINE: They play tennis after class. {page_007_004.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f1-04.mp3}

VOCAB: soccer
LINE: Carlos plays soccer on Saturdays. {page_007_005.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f1-05.mp3}

VOCAB: basketball
LINE: Carl plays basketball at school. {page_007_006.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f1-06.mp3}

# --- Figure 2: hear a sentence, tap the matching picture ---
# SHARED option pool (the six pictures) declared once; each item gives ANSWER + its clip.
$SELECT Figure 2: Which sport?
INTRO: Listen to each sentence and tap the picture it describes.
INSTRUCTION: Tap the matching picture.
OPTION: a | {page_008_001.jpg}
OPTION: b | {page_008_002.jpg}
OPTION: c | {page_008_003.jpg}
OPTION: d | {page_008_004.jpg}
OPTION: e | {page_008_005.jpg}
OPTION: f | {page_008_006.jpg}

PROMPT: Tony and Jim watch soccer games on TV. {bk04-l1a-f2-01.mp3}
ANSWER: e

PROMPT: Betty and Jane are playing tennis. {bk04-l1a-f2-02.mp3}
ANSWER: d

PROMPT: Mark plays baseball. {bk04-l1a-f2-03.mp3}
ANSWER: c

PROMPT: My children play with a ball after school. {bk04-l1a-f2-04.mp3}
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: The basketball game is at eight o'clock tonight. {bk04-l1a-f2-05.mp3}
ANSWER: f

# --- Figure 3: hear Q&A, tap the statement that is true (options differ per item) ---
$SELECT Figure 3: Likes and doesn't like
INTRO: Listen to each short conversation, then tap the sentence that is true.
INSTRUCTION: Tap the correct sentence.
SHOW_PROMPT

PROMPT: John, do you like football games? — No, I don't. {bk04-l1a-f3-01.mp3}
OPTION: a | John likes football games.
OPTION: b | John doesn't like football games.
ANSWER: b
# +AUDIO per item below

PROMPT: Jack and Joe, do you like sports? — Yes, we do.
OPTION: a | Jack and Joe like sports.
OPTION: b | Jack and Joe don't like sports.
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: Mr. Adams, do you like basketball? — Yes, I do.
OPTION: a | Mr. Adams likes basketball.
OPTION: b | Mr. Adams doesn't like basketball.
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: Do you like baseball? — No, we don't.
OPTION: a | They like baseball.
OPTION: b | They don't like baseball.
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: Donna, do you like tennis? — Yes, I do.
OPTION: a | Donna likes tennis.
OPTION: b | Donna doesn't like tennis.
ANSWER: a

# --- Figure 4: answer the question -> PRODUCE (defaults: INPUT speak, CHECK reveal) ---
$PRODUCE Figure 4: Answer the questions
INTRO: Listen to the statement and question, then answer out loud. (You can switch to typing if it's easier.)
INSTRUCTION: Say your answer, then check.

EXAMPLE
PROMPT: The children play ball in the afternoon. What do the children like to do in the afternoon? {bk04-l1a-f4-00-p.mp3}
RESPONSE: The children like to play ball in the afternoon. {bk04-l1a-f4-00-a.mp3}
# +AUDIO (prompt & answer) per item below

PROMPT: Sue and Kate go to football games on weekends. What do Sue and Kate like to do on weekends?
RESPONSE: They like to go to football games on weekends.

PROMPT: Jim swims at the base on Saturdays. What does Jim like to do on Saturdays?
RESPONSE: Jim likes to swim at the base on Saturdays.

PROMPT: Mr. and Mrs. Adams play tennis every morning. What do Mr. and Mrs. Adams like to do every morning?
RESPONSE: Mr. and Mrs. Adams like to play tennis every morning.

PROMPT: Jack watches basketball on Fridays. What does Jack like to watch on Fridays?
RESPONSE: Jack likes to watch basketball on Fridays.

# --- Figure 5: repeat sentences (map) — separate vocab line per item ---
$DIALOGUE Figure 5: Cities and Towns in Texas
REPEAT
INTRO: Look at the map of Texas and repeat the words and sentences.
INSTRUCTION: Listen and repeat.

VOCAB: cities
VOCAB: towns
LINE: Texas has big cities and small towns. {page_010_001.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f5-01.mp3}

VOCAB: lives
LINE: The King family lives in a small town.

VOCAB: city
LINE: The Soto family lives in the city of Dallas.

VOCAB: visits
LINE: Sometimes, the King family visits the Soto family in Dallas.

LINE: Los Angeles, New York and Chicago are also big cities. These cities are not in Texas.

# --- Figure 6: hear a question, tap the correct answer ---
$SELECT Figure 6: Choose the correct answer
INTRO: Listen to each question and tap the correct answer.
INSTRUCTION: Tap the correct answer.

PROMPT: My sister has a house in San Antonio. She works in San Antonio. What does she do in San Antonio? {bk04-l1a-f6-01.mp3}
OPTION: a | She works in San Antonio.
OPTION: b | She plays sports in San Antonio.
ANSWER: a
# +AUDIO per item below

PROMPT: Joe lives in New York City. Where does he live?
OPTION: a | He lives in a small town.
OPTION: b | He lives in a big city.
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: Jacksonville is not on the map. It's very small. Is it a city or a town?
OPTION: a | It's a town.
OPTION: b | It's a city.
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: Mary is at her friend's house. They are talking. What's Mary doing?
OPTION: a | Mary is sleeping.
OPTION: b | Mary is visiting her friend.
ANSWER: b

# --- Figure 7: sound discrimination J vs Y — SHARED option pool (same a/b every item) ---
$SELECT Figure 7: /j/ as in "jet" or /y/ as in "yet"?
INTRO: Listen to each word. Tap a for the /j/ sound (as in "jet") or b for the /y/ sound (as in "yet").
INSTRUCTION: Tap the sound you hear.
OPTION: a | /j/ — as in "jet"
OPTION: b | /y/ — as in "yet"

EXAMPLE
PROMPT: jam {bk04-l1a-f7-00.mp3}
ANSWER: a
# +AUDIO per item below

PROMPT: joke
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: year
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: you
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: jaw
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: join
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: yes
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: yard
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: juice
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: jay
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: use
ANSWER: b

# --- Figure 8: listening passage + comprehension (ONE figure -> TWO activities) ---
# Passage: each sentence its own LINE (own clip when sliced).
$DIALOGUE Figure 8: Linda's Week
INTRO: Listen to the paragraph about Linda.
INSTRUCTION: Listen.

Narrator: This is Linda. {page_012_001.jpg} {bk04-l1a-f8-01.mp3}

Narrator: Linda works in an office. She works from Monday to Friday — she works all week long.

Narrator: On Saturdays, Linda gets up early and cleans her house all morning long.

Narrator: After she cleans, she starts to cook. She likes to cook a big dinner for her friends; she starts to cook the meal at 2 p.m. and cooks all afternoon long.

Narrator: Her friends come at 6:30. Sometimes they watch a show on TV, and sometimes they talk. Linda likes their visits very much.

$SELECT Figure 8: Linda's Week — comprehension
INTRO: Listen again and tap the correct word for each sentence.
INSTRUCTION: Tap the correct word.
SHOW_PROMPT

PROMPT: Linda works ____.
OPTION: a | all night long
OPTION: b | all week long
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: On Saturdays, she ____ her house.
OPTION: a | cleans
OPTION: b | cooks
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: She ____ a big dinner, and she ____ to cook the meal at 2:00.
OPTION: a | cooks / starts
OPTION: b | cleans / ends
ANSWER: a

PROMPT: Sometimes they watch a ____ on TV.
OPTION: a | game
OPTION: b | show
ANSWER: b

PROMPT: Linda likes her friends' ____ very much.
OPTION: a | visits
OPTION: b | houses
ANSWER: a
